<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by Dorien Karei on 05-10-2002 01:14 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">     Yes, Ragon, I guess I can see how my incident with the lock picking bug can be thought of as funny now, lol, but while I was going through it, it wasn't, since during my panic of trying to get it to quit, I found myself being chased by the original 5 orcs attached to the noses I attempted to pick lock, that 5 which again, during my panic turned into 22 orcs chasing me while I was still running around, or should I say, sliding around in pick locking position, when I finally realized that maybe making a 2nd attempt at picking one of thier noses would cause the game to snap out of it, which it did, I just had to work the orcs to get one alone long enough to try, that was not fun at the time.

     Also, I've been playing the demo again, and, I didn't want to say anything earlier, I figured maybe it was just me, but I think there is a bug with the stat system.  At first, when I would level up, I would notice when I use my stat points and accept the changes, the changes don't take place, the actual stat changes yes, but the extras, what the main stats also change, the ones that show when you sit your cursor over the main stats(str, dex etc.), they're not changed, I have to close the stats window and reopen it, THEN the stats are changed, ok, no biggy there...but the one that I can't let go that just ocurred, I had leveled up and had added points to strength, making a total of 25, closed the window, and about 2 min later I looked at the stat window again, and poof, it was at 21, now, before I leveled, it was 21, I had added 4 points, suddenly it was back to 21 again, from 25, so I walked around with the window closed for about 10 minutes, then 20, it stayed at 21...if ya ask me, that's not a pretty bug.

[This message has been edited by Dorien Karei (edited 10-05-2002).]</TEXTAREA>
